{"履修期": "秋学期", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "This course examines how businesses contribute to the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) through corporate strategy, operations, governance, and green finance, with a strong focus on Japan.Students first build a foundation in sustainability and SDGs in a business context. Thus, students will progressively deepen their understanding by analyzing corporate strategy and green finance through real-world cases of Japanese companies, global firms operating in Japan, and Japan-specific policy/ finance cases.&nbsp;", "到達目標": "By the end of this course, students are expected to be able to:1. Understand basic concepts of sustainability, ESG, and green finance.2. Explain how companies integrate sustainability into business strategy.3. Recognize how sustainability relates to financial performance and long-term success.4. Compare sustainability practices in Japan with those in other regions.5. Present and discuss sustainable business ideas clearly.", "特記事項": "", "関連科目": "", "授業の概要・背景": "", "授業方法": "Short lectures introducing key concepts.&nbsp;Case-based discussions using Japanese company examples.&nbsp;Group work and presentations.&nbsp;Short reflection assignments linking theory, cases, and SDGs.&nbsp;Use of public materials such as sustainability reports, corporate websites, policy documents, and media articles.", "トピック": {"第1回": ["<span style=\"font-family:-webkit-standard,serif;font-size:10pt;line-height:15.333332px;background-image:none;background-position:0% 0%;background-size:auto;background-repeat:repeat;background-attachment:scroll;background-origin:padding-box;background-clip:border-box;\"><span style=\"font-family:-webkit-standard;font-size:13.28px;\">【Startup Week】<br /></span><span style=\"font-family:-webkit-standard;font-size:13.28px;\">Online class（Task-oriented format)</span></span><div><span style=\"font-family:-webkit-standard,serif;font-size:10pt;line-height:15.333332px;background-image:none;background-position:0% 0%